article.headline: Wright St. 77, Cal St.-Fullerton 62
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 19 points and Wright State's bench supplied 38 points in a 77-62 victory over Cal State-Fullerton on Satuday night. Vaughn Duggins added 15 points, Will Graham 12 and Scottie Wilson 11 -- all in substitute roles -- for the Raiders (21-8), who won their ninth game in a row. Wright State shot 50 percent from the field and hit 9-of-20 3-pointers. Scott Cutley had 20 points and Bobby Brown 12 -- eight below his average -- for the Titans (18-7), who lost back-to-back games for the first time this season. They fell to Long Beach State 94-84 on Wednesday night. Fullerton led 34-33 at the break but the Raiders pulled away at the outset of the second half. The Titans closed to within 55-49 with 8 minutes left but Wright State went on a 7-0 lead to put the game out of reach. Wright State trailed by as many as 12 points in the first half but hit 7 of its last 11 shots from the field to pull within a point.
